Please indicate how well the following statements describe you:


I daydream and fantasize, with some regularity, about things that might happen to me.
column16: I often have tender, concerned feelings for people less fortunate than me.
column17: I sometimes find it difficult to see things from the "other guy's" point of view.
column18: Sometimes I don't feel very sorry for other people when they are having problems.
column19: I really get involved with the feelings of the characters in a novel.
column20: In emergency situations, I feel apprehensive and ill-at-ease.
column21:
I am usually objective when I watch a movie or play, and I don't often get completely
caught up in it.
column22: I try to look at everybody's side of a disagreement before I make a decision.
column23: When I see someone being taken advantage of, I feel kind of protective towards them.
column24: I sometimes feel helpless when I am in the middle of a very emotional situation.
column25:
I sometimes try to understand my friends better by imagining how things look from
their perspective.
column26: Becoming extremely involved in a good book or movie is somewhat rare for me.
column27: When I see someone get hurt, I tend to remain calm.
column28: Other people's misfortunes do not usually disturb me a great deal.
column29:
If I'm sure I'm right about something, I don't waste much time listening to other
people's arguments.
column30: After seeing a play or movie, I have felt as though I were one of the characters.
column31: Being in a tense emotional situation scares me
column32:
When I see someone being treated unfairly, I sometimes don't feel very much pity for
them
column33: I am usually pretty effective in dealing with emergencies.
column34: I am often quite touched by things that I see happen
column35: I believe that there are two sides to every question and try to look at them both.
column36: I would describe myself as a pretty soft-hearted person.
column37:
When I watch a good movie, I can very easily put myself in the place of a leading
character.
column38: I tend to lose control during emergencies.
column39: When I'm upset at someone, I usually try to "put myself in his shoes" for a while.
column40:
When I am reading an interesting story or novel, I imagine how I would feel if the
events in the story were happening to me.
column41: When I see someone who badly needs help in an emergency, I go to pieces.
column42: Before criticizing somebody, I try to imagine how I would feel if I were in their place.
